card0.name: Pikachu
card0.description: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

card1.name: Charizard
card1.description: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

card2.name: Bulbasaur
card2.description: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this POKéMON.

card3.name: Squirtle
card3.description: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. Powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.

card4.name: Caterpie
card4.description: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

card5.name: Weedle
card5.description: Often found in forests, eating leaves. It has a sharp venomous stinger on its head.

card6.name: Pidgey
card6.description: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

card7.name: Rattata
card7.description: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.

card8.name: Spearow
card8.description: Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speed to stay airborne.

card9.name: Ekans
card9.description: Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole.

65a6c3c02c175.name: Aipom
65a6c3c02c175.description: As it did more and more with its tail, its hands became clumsy. It makes its nest high in the treetops.

65a6c3f7c2404.name: Growlithe
65a6c3f7c2404.description: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

65a6c496bded7.name: Clefairy
65a6c496bded7.description: It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.

65a6c4c50e6b8.name: Vulpix
65a6c4c50e6b8.description: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.

65a6c5072f215.name: Dugtrio
65a6c5072f215.description: Its three heads bob separately up and down to loosen the soil nearby, making it easier for it to burrow.

65a6c52f7981d.name: Poliwhirl
65a6c52f7981d.description: Staring at the swirl on its belly causes drowsiness. This trait of Poliwhirl’s has been used in place of lullabies to get children to go to sleep.

65a6c56156084.name: Machop
65a6c56156084.description: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it’s the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.

65a6c5a29c316.name: Slowpoke
65a6c5a29c316.description: It is incredibly slow and dopey. It takes five seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

65a6c67b78ae8.name: Ponyta
65a6c67b78ae8.description: About an hour after birth, Ponyta’s fiery mane and tail grow out, giving the Pokémon an impressive appearance.

65a6c7064bd04.name: Dewgong
65a6c7064bd04.description: Its entire body is a snowy white. Unharmed by even intense cold, it swims powerfully in icy waters.

65a6c7aa73ebc.name: Gengar
65a6c7aa73ebc.description: To steal the life of its target, it slips into the prey’s shadow and silently waits for an opportunity.

65a6c7dba505e.name: Horsea
65a6c7dba505e.description: Horsea makes its home in oceans with gentle currents. If this Pokémon is under attack, it spits out pitch-black ink and escapes.

65a6c8052edf2.name: Eevee
65a6c8052edf2.description: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

65a6c82b4b6fa.name: Croconaw
65a6c82b4b6fa.description: Once Croconaw has clamped its jaws on its foe, it will absolutely not let go. Because the tips of its fangs are forked back like barbed fishhooks, they become impossible to remove when they have sunk in.

65a6c96e7076d.name: Teddiursa
65a6c96e7076d.description: This Pokémon discreetly follows Combee to find their hive. It scoops up big dollops of honey in its palms to eat.
